name: Warung Babi Guling Andi Jaya Perean
address: Jl. Perean Tengah, Perean Tengah, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1:
One of my fav babi guling in Tabanan. Always coming here if I pass by.

They're using brown rice as their signature. All tasted good but I never got the pig skin crispy no matter what time I came to eat. üòÇ

The price was reasonable. The place is as cozy as you can get in a bigul restaurant.
review 2: Great place to stop by for food if you are travelling up north. Pork was soft and tender and the fried pork cracking was really flavourful. They also serve with brown rice. Service was fast and it seems like a standard order, there was no menu. We enjoyed the food a lot.
review 3: small, no frills warung but the food is excellent. plenty of parking. service is super fast. was busy but not too crowded and seems to be popular with the locals. great place to stop on the way or back from points north. highly recommended.
review 4: Babi Guling, fast service, good taste you can park in front. Reasonable price.
review 5: Pretty cheap place, food was a bit too salty & chili wasn't spicy. Neither the best nor worst babi guling I've had.

name: DEPOT MULA SARI
address: Jl. Perean Tengah, Perean Tengah, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: Very relaxing place with amazing food for cheap prices, very accessible right on the road, definitely a very nice place to stop by if you are on the road
review 2: Fantastic restaurant quiet on the road to singaraja... perfect place to stop with lovely service for a coffee drink or food.
review 3: Recommended ....nice place to bring the family for lunch.great servise

name: Warung Mama Deva
address: Jl. Denpasar-Singaraja No.300, Perean Tengah, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
The owner is so friendly, and the food is also (the food price is not more than idr 30k). I recommend this restaurant to try since everything is great.

FYI the nyat nyat menu is a bit spicy
review 2:
Super delicious grilled chicken and nyat nyat chicken.

Owner and staff were so friendly to us. Wel priced too. Went there twice in 2 days
review 3: Very good food, cheap, very kind staff and fantastic view on the sunset, recommend!!
review 4: Good food to try and the owner is friendly, price affordable
review 5: Every menu is delicious, this is me and my family favorite
